HEADWORD: Gloaming
<hw>Gloam"ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Gloom</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Twilight; dusk; the fall of the evening.</def>
<mark>[Scot. & North of Eng., and in poetry.]</mark>
<rj><au>Hogg.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Sullenness; melancholy.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>J. Still.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gloar</ent>⟦br⟧
